  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "But he spake the more vehemently,.... With a louder voice; with more spirit and eagerness; in a more peremptory and self-confident way. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "If I should die with thee, I will not deny thee in any wise. The Syriac version adds, \"O my Lord\", my dear Lord, I will never deny thee upon any consideration whatever; and the Persic version, O Lord: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "likewise also said they all; as he said, so said \"all the disciples\", as the Syriac version reads it; See Gill on Matthew 26:35. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "likewise also said they all; as he said, so said \"all the disciples\", as the Syriac version reads it; See Gill on ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Matthew 26:35",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
