  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Expositor's Greek Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Mark 14:31",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἐκπερισσῶς",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", abundantly in matter and manner, with vehemence and iteration; a ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἅπαξ λεγ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἐλάλει",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", kept saying: that he would not deny his Master even if he had to die for it.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ὡσαύτως",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", a stronger word than Mt.’s ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ὁμοίως",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " = in the same way, and probably in the same words. But the words of the others were simply a faint echo of Peter’s vehement and copious talk. They feebly said once (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἔλεγον",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " = ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "εἶπον",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") what he said strongly again and again (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἐλάλει",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ").",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
